The paper deals with the development and comparison of different machine learning models for travel mode inference using GPS trajectories. The models include Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are both popular machine learning techniques used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves data preprocessing and feature engineering, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography (cs.CR).
